==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tube-nosed
<hw>Tube"-nosed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Having the nostrils prolonged in the form of horny
tubes along the sides of the beak; -- said of certain sea birds.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Belonging to the Tubinares.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tuber</ent>⟦br⟧
